Sadly I can't give this one a thumbs up! They are clearly terrified of the crowds and the baby goats are being separated from their mothers and many have a horrible fate and are butchered by inexperienced people. Nothing against you personally or your kind Omani friend, as you are simply showing the reality without sugar coating it. I just wish people would let their culture evolve into something kinder. We in the west are not better so this is not direct criticism directed at any specific nation.. just my general view. I think Omanis are lovely hospitable people, I just wish some parts of the culture would evolve.

@Cook Chef My reply to John Zamer clarifies what I meant by '' evolve ''. I meant WE could evolve our ethics as people, a single planet. This was NOT an insult on any religion! It's in fact probably much worse in the west, and too many atrocities to list, I agree. I have watched the documentary '' Earthlings '' and it shows it's bad everywhere. I have always defended Islam when people have criticised it, particularly because such poison as alcohol is forbidden in Islam and I see the damage it causes to people in the west and this hurts me. I don't disagree the intention of Halal is to cause the least minimum pain, sadly, some of the people who take the animals home are not always experienced butchers and therefore, it becomes haram. I have witnessed it with my own eyes during the Eid al Adha when my neighbours (who are not butchers!) were hacking away at a sheep. If only people on here could take comments such as mine with more compassion we could have a respectful conversation.
